SnoutSec â€“ Facial Recognition

This project implements a web interface for real-time facial recognition, using the deviceâ€™s camera and a Flask backend.
How to Run

1.Open the terminal and navigate to the project folder:

cd "face_recognition - copy"


2. Activate your Conda environment:

conda activate face_env


3. Export the Flask app that will log users and timestamps:

export FLASK_APP=attendance_app.py


4. Run Flask to access via localhost:

flask run


5. Open your browser and visit:

http://127.0.0.1:5000


6. Allow camera permissions when prompted.

ğŸš€ Features

Real-time webcam video capture.

Biometric facial recognition.

Display of authenticated user info:

Name

ID

Login time

Responsive interface styled with Tailwind CSS.

Simple 3-step authentication flow:

User positions face in front of the camera.

The system performs facial recognition.

A digital credential is issued instantly.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

Frontend:

HTML5

TailwindCSS

JavaScript (camera handling + overlay)

Backend (example stack):

Flask (Python) to serve templates (url_for)

Computer vision libraries (OpenCV, dlib, face-recognition)

ğŸ“¸ Demonstration

Usage flow:

The user positions their face in front of the camera.

The system detects and recognizes the face.

Credentials are displayed on-screen.

Login is logged into a .csv / Excel sheet.

